  "prompt": "How should I start preparing for CLAT 2017?",
  "response": "To prepare for CLAT 2017, follow these steps:\n\n1. Understand the Exam Pattern\n- Familiarize yourself with the CLAT exam pattern\n- Total 200 multiple-choice questions\n- 2-hour duration\n- Sections: English, General Knowledge, Legal Reasoning, Logical Reasoning, and Elementary Mathematics\n\n2. Study Materials\n- CLAT preparation books\n- Previous years' question papers\n- Mock test series\n- Online study resources\n\n3. Subject-wise Preparation Strategy\n- English: Focus on comprehension, grammar, vocabulary\n- General Knowledge: Read newspapers, magazines, current affairs\n- Legal Reasoning: Study basic legal concepts and landmark cases\n- Logical Reasoning: Practice puzzles and analytical questions\n- Mathematics: Focus on basic mathematical concepts\n\n4. Recommended Study Schedule\n- Dedicate 2-3 hours daily\n- Create a balanced study plan\n- Cover all sections systematically\n- Practice mock tests regularly\n\n5. Additional Tips\n- Join a coaching institute or online coaching\n- Take regular mock tests\n- Time management is crucial\n- Stay updated with current affairs\n- Work on weak areas\n\n6. Resources\n- Newspapers: The Hindu, Indian Express\n- Magazines: Competition Success Review\n- Online platforms: CLAT Possible, LST, TIME\n\nStart early and maintain consistent preparation.",
